<HEADLINE>
BOTTENFIELD TO RETURN, SAYS SHOULDER OK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(OPTIONAL: Updates second item) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Kent Bottenfield returns to the starting
rotation tonight after missing two starts because of tendinitis in
his right shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Bottenfield came to the Anaheim Angels from the St. Louis
Cardinals in the trade for Jim Edmonds after winning 18 games in
1999.
</P>
<P>
   He is 4-5 with a 5.21 ERA, but some of his problems can be
linked to his sore shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Bottenfield first felt something was wrong in the shoulder in
mid-May, but he tried to pitch through it. His results showed there
was something wrong.
</P>
<P>
   In his first eight starts this season, Bottenfield allowed three
earned runs or fewer seven times. But in his past five starts, he
allowed fewer than three earned runs only once.
</P>
<P>
   Though the shoulder affected his control, Bottenfield said he
had great command of his pitches during a simulated game Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was able to control the ball for 65 pitches, which I've not
been able to do for quite some time,'' he said. ``I expect to go
out there (tonight) and throw anywhere from 100 to 115 pitches. I
don't expect to feel anything in my shoulder, just be normal.''
</P>
<P>
   Bottenfield said the two weeks off were good for him in that he
worked hard on his conditioning, building up leg strength and
losing some weight.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had some definite goals in mind for the two weeks,'' he
said. ``It was something I needed to do to keep me busy and not
just sitting around.''
</P>
<P>
   Dickson to have surgery: Pitcher Jason Dickson said he will have
arthroscopic surgery on his right shoulder. The procedure will be
performed Tuesday by Dr. Lewis Yocum.
</P>
<P>
   Dickson had surgery to repair a torn labrum in March of 1999 and
missed the entire 1999 season. He came back and made the starting
rotation out of spring training, but landed on the DL with a
strained hip.
</P>
<P>
   But after coming back from the strained hip, he began to feel
pain in his shoulder, possibly a result of favoring the hip. He
landed on the DL a second time.
</P>
<P>
   While on a rehab assignment, the shoulder pain became too much
to ignore, and Dickson finally told trainers.
</P>
<P>
   Depending on the extent of the damage in the shoulder, the
surgery could be season-ending.
</P>
<P>
   ``Maybe it's something mechanical, with the way I throw,''
Dickson said of his recurring shoulder troubles. ``Maybe my labrum
is weak. Maybe it was reinjured during rehab. You really don't
know.''
</P>
<P>
   Stocker out: Shortstop Kevin Stocker was a late scratch Friday
night because of a sore left knee. Benji Gil started in Stocker's
place.
</P>
</TEXT>
