<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NY-MENINGITIS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MENINGITIS KILLS AIR PASSENGER SOON AFTER ARRIVAL 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A 20-year-old Rochester, N.Y., man died of meningitis
two hours after his flight from Israel landed in Newark, N.J., on
Friday. On Saturday, authorities were notifying the plane's other
passengers that they might want to seek medical advice.
</P>
<P>
   When the Rochester man, Joseph Ferraro, arrived at Newark
International Airport aboard El Al Flight 17 about 5 p.m. Friday,
airline workers notified Port Authority police that he needed
medical assistance. Paramedics took him to Beth Israel Medical
Center in Newark, where he was pronounced dead at 7:07 p.m.,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The jet was carrying 416 passengers and 19 crew members. Gregory
Trevor, a spokesman for the Port Authority, said that as of early
Saturday afternoon, authorities had contacted 14 passengers,
encouraging those who had concerns about possible infection to see
a doctor.
</P>
<P>
   Trevor said that federal and state health officials had also
been notified of Ferraro's illness _ meningococcal meningitis, a
bacterial infection of the membranes around the brain and spinal
cord. The infection is transmitted only through close contact with
an infected person, and it is treatable with antibiotics if
detected early enough.
</P>
<P>
   He apparently was traveling in Israel on a program for Jewish
teen-agers and college-age youth.
</P>
<P>
   Neither organizers of the trip nor Ferraro's family could be
reached for comment Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-24-00 1734EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
