   VIENNA - Apart from the traditional sites of this seat of
onetime Austrian royalty is a quite-uncommon house whose courtyard
faces the Danube Canal in a neighborhood where there are no
palaces. What makes the building appear unusual are the windows. No
two are alike. This is KunstHausWien, a privately-operated and
sponsored museum that pays homage to the art and architectural
representations of a most unusual man, Friedensreich Hundertwasser.
(Kleinberg, Cox News Service). MOVED Wednesday. WITH PHOTO.
